Again the Brisket was really good.< /review>

<Rate>5< /Rate>< text>
REAL TALK!!! I've been hearing about this place on the radio so last night I stopped by. I got the brisket and ribs, w/Mac, beans and potato salad and cornbread. I love tender meat. This meat was delicious...tender, seasoned and cooked. The mac,beans are potato salad were excellent. They need to work on that cornbread...too much cornmeal and don't be scared to let the muffins brown a little. I loved the sauce-a perfect blend of what you want BBQ sauce to be with a lil kick that perfectly compliments the tender, perfectly seasoned meat.  A little pricey for take out (nearly$40, w/no drink). However, if this place survives the pandemic it is going to be something special in a little sit down dining spot. Overall the food was magnificent.  I'll definitely be back.<//text>

Bee Green Recycling and Supply is a great resource. <user>111997462188720782136< /user>< Text>
Good spot to get rid of your s***. A few tips:

The location given here (725 Independent) is for the C&D Yard, where you'll probably bring most of your stuff. But if you're bringing concrete, bricks, rock, dirt, shingles, or green waste, go to the second location a few blocks north on Coliseum, the Inert and Green Waste Yard (5900 Coliseum).

I sat in line for 30mins on a Saturday at the C&D Yard and when I pulled up they sent me to the other location because I was dumping concrete. I brought a load of bricks later. The good part: the rates are cheaper and there was no line.

I paid ~$110 today to dump two loads of concrete and brick, about 2600 pounds.

Map and rates in photos.</Text>

< text>
I have mixed feelings about this place.  The remodel attempted to make it "Applebees meets Chuck E Cheese", but the restaurant is simply not big enough to make it really work as it just feels cramped.  The arcade room is a nice idea, but is too small to be more than a one time novelty for the kids....and they ended up losing the back room (you can no longer reserve a space for birthday parties unless you have 20 people!).  The food is pricey for what you get, the wait times are horrendous on Friday and Saturday nights, and the mostly teenage staff is apathetic and generally useless (the remodel didn't help at all with that!)

Having said all of that, the pizza is still good and it is nice to watch a game at the bar.  It's also nice to have a restaurant in Paradise that does not have that God-awful 1950s theme.  The microbrew selection is pretty good, too.  Overall, it's an OK place to go every once in awhile, but I certainly wouldn't put it in the regular eating-out rotation list.<//text>

If you‚Äôre looking for a good place to live and raise kids, keep on looking!! This place is the opposite of what you‚Äôre looking for. I moved in January of 2018 and regret even stepping foot on property. Before signing lease, they showed me a unit that was updated and looked really nice and was told my unit would be the same. I paid my deposit to move in 4 weeks later. Between the 4 weeks I have turned in all paperwork needed in order to move in, including my ESA (Emotional Support Animal) paperwork. It was 2 weeks before move in and I messaged and called in to make sure I was all good for move in day. I left messages and emails and no one ever got back to me. I was about to look for another place till finally 1 day before move in someone answers my call and tells me everything is good. On move in day, none of my paperwork was ready and the unit wasn‚Äôt even ready. And they charged me an additional $450 to move in with out explaining what for. It took 2 hours to get the paperwork ready and even then, the paperwork was all messed up. When I got to my unit, the place was disgusting. There were cobwebs all across the ceiling, layers and layers of dust, the place smelt like an ashtray and it looked absolutely nothing like the unit I was shown. To add on top of that, I was given a mail key that opened other peoples mailboxes and didn‚Äôt receive mine till 3 months later and trying to contact the office in those three months and never receiving a phone call back or even returned emails. Finally after almost 4 months of trying to get ahold of the office, someone returns my call. After explaining my stressful and horrific experience since being a resident, all they could say is ‚ÄúWe have new management and there‚Äôs nothing we can do about it.‚Äù They received a new management when we first moved in, I would think after 4 months things should be running smoothly but no, they just blammed it on new management. I decided to take a look at my lease to see if there is anything I can do, and come to find out the lease they have on my file is no where near the lease I signed on move in. On the lease they have on my file, they charged me an extra $450 for my ESA, which is illegal and charged me per month. So I decided to contact the property management, even they don‚Äôt return calls nor answer emails. After about my fifth time trying to contact property management, they call me back. 103251967729944527646< /user>
<review>This is an excellent pet hospital. It is the cleanest that I have been to in the area and has no odors, as a hospital should be. They are also caring and professional from my experience.

I took my 17 year old cat Max here after reading all the positive reviews. She was unable to eat or drink anything and acting very confused, I knew something was very wrong. I left her overnight to receive IV fluids and medication. When I went back I was told her unfortunate diagnosis. Unfortunately she was suffering from kidney failure and an intestinal blockage. It was delicately brought up that putting her to sleep was probably for the best because she was suffering and was too weak for an operation. They could have recommended more treatments and it would have cost more money, but Dr. Troxel knew my Max was suffering and told me the truth. Her honesty was very much appreciated.

It was the hardest decision of my life. I grew up with my Max cat from my teens, 20's and into my 30's. She was always there for me. They gave me so much time before having to decide and when I did, they gave me even more time to say goodbye and call family to say their goodbyes to Max. Never once did I feel rushed during this difficult time. Looking into her emerald green eyes as she went to sleep broke my heart and still does. I was a complete mess and never have grieved like that before. I'm just so grateful that the staff and Dr. Troxel were professional and understanding.

I took the loss of my Max extremely hard, I'm still struggling but getting through it day by day. The staff even sent a sympathy card and they signed it all with comforting messages. That was very much appreciated and touched my heart during my mourning. It is not every pet hospital that takes extra time and cares about their patients. Picking up the ashes of my Max made me emotional and speechless but they offer such a beautiful cremation package. I was honestly in shock by how nice the wooden box, name tag and everything was. Holding my Max's paw print again made me smile. It just felt like it was done with honor and respect and gave me comfort.

This was my first experience at the East Valley Pet Hospital and when my heart is ready for another pet I will most certainly be back. I highly recommend you bring your beloved pet here. They are professional, caring, and respectful. Thank you to the staff and Dr. Troxel from myself and my family.<//review><rate>5<//rate><name>David Ramos</name></record></dataset><record>

< text>
I moved to the area and had no established vet for my dog. She ate a 7oz Hershey kiss... the whole thing! I took her here with very little expectations. The staff was very professional, explaining the payment process at each step of the visit which I like because I felt I knew beforehand what they wanted to do before they did it and how much it would cost. I ended up having to put her to sleep that day due to kidney failure. Again the staff was very professional and knew how to handle this stressful situation with dignity  and respect for myself and my dog. The Dr was very compassionate  but not overly sappy which I liked. He gave me all my options and was very thorough in reading all the results.  He was supportive of my decision and when he came in to put her to sleep he even asked God to please forgive him and was very sensitive to my dog even though I am sure he has to do this all the time. A week later they sent me a personalized card with their sympthy. When I got my dog's remains they came in a beautiful cedar  box with her paw print, a bit of her hair, and seeds to grow to remember her by. This far exceeded  my expectations and was very sweet closure for my two boys. Overall I would definitely  recommend  this vet hospital and will certainly take my next pet there.< /text>

I was pleased that although I did not have an appointment, because I was worried about my cat's medical condition, I was encouraged to come in and wait for an opening in the schedule, an opportunity I greatly appreciated!!! I waited about an hour, which was very reasonable for a non-appointment.
Dr. Graham treated my cat Wonder very professionally, examining her thoroughly for the extreme constipation we suspected. She spoke very specifically and knowledgeably to me, suggesting different scenarios for  what Wonder's  exact problem could be, and offering some solutions.

I returned several hours later to pick Wonder up after her enema . The office staff was lovely and gave me specific directions on how to administer the medicine orally. <GmapID>0x80db55b87a41f5bd:0xb08f40ee2910de95</GmapID><Review>One thing I urge people to remember is doctors of any sort can have good and bad reviews based on the patient preference. I feel the same way with Vets. I absolutely love my dog and heard great things about East Valley Pet Hospital but almost didn't bring him in because of the yelp reviews.

I had just gotten off work and pretty much every vet in the area was closing, including the vet I had originally set up in town when I moved to Redlands not too long ago. I was hesitant but I really wanted to take my poor doggie in to get him checked out for a mystery lump that had caused him to not want to use his hind leg.

I AM SO GLAD I DID! The office has a very pleasant receptionist who just started a week ago at this facility. She was very nice and very attentive. I did not have an appointment and they were doing their shot clinic so I was very worried when I walked up that I would be there FORVER, but I was attended to immediately, got all the forms filled out and sat down. I only waited about 20 minutes, which if you are a pet owner who has made appointments at the vet before you know 20 is absolutely fantastic. Especially after not even having an appointment.

The Nurse(Vet assistant) and the Dr. were very nice! they were gentle and calming and talked to my dog just like the rest of us crazy animal lovers.

The fact that they are open later than other vets in the area AND 7 days a week gives them a little more justification if their prices are a few dollars higher than some of the local vets. The Office Visit cost was $45 dollars, I am not sure if they have separate pricelists for non-appointment and appointment but $45 was not out of the ordinary for a vet visit in my opinion but a lot of people say they are a bit more expensive than Redlands is used to. I will gladly pay that again in a non-life threatening emergency visit for my dog, I didn't need to make an appointment, they saw me within a half hour of getting there, they were pleasant and gentle and they knew what was wrong without convincing me to do some sort of outlandish testing that costs in the thousands ( I had a vet in yorba linda do that 2 years ago, an x ray for gas! he wanted to make sure there wasn't any underlying causes...)<//Review><user>103806293024260312959<//user><name>Melissa Salazar</name>< pics>
None</pics>
</record></dataset><record>

<time>1492808175051< /time><review>If I could give 10 stars I would!! In all seriouslness this is the best place to take your furry family members. I recently had to say goodbye to my 15 year old cat Bubba and they helped to make it the best experience considering the circumstances. Dr. Troxel was incredibly patient while we asked questions, and very kind and comforting during the entire process. The receptionist was kind and talked to us while we checked in. The assistant that came in to walk through the paperwork was kind and patient and even offered to have the receptionist come to the room for the payment and signatures instead of us having to go to the front desk all teary eyed and emotional. Literally everyone was kind, patient, caring, and offered their condolences. You can guarantee that I am going to recommend this place to anyone and everyone. I had previously taken my pets (emergent visits) to the hospital in Grand Terrace, and regular visits to the Redlands Animal Hospital, and they are great, but East Valley Pet Hospital is outstanding in the truest sense of the word. I was surprised to see that the fee for aftercare includes a company that scatters the ashes of your furry loved one in the ocean. I was touched that less than a week later I also received a card from the staff offering their kind words, along with a footprint of my little guy on the card. The facility is clean and welcoming. <review>Whenever I'm in the Roseville area, Blue House is my go-to spot. We ended up stumbling upon Jiu Jiu after being told there is going to be a long wait at Blue House.

We called Jiu Jiu and asked how long wait was and they told us there was no wait right now. We got there we were seated right away. The menu is pretty extensive and it all one price. There are alucard items that are not included in the all you can eat menu, but the AYCE menu is really awesome. This place is authentically Korean and there are definitely a ton of families that come here.

Service can be a little bit slow at times just because I don't think they have enough staff, but overall it's decent! I've been here twice and have not been disappointed at all. They also have a ton of side options like ramen, or cold noodles. I highly suggest getting the boiled dumplings because they're so good! The plaza it's in is kind of sketch at night time because they are the only thing open besides the liquor store on the corner. This place is definitely a hidden gem!< /review><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Resp>None< /Resp><gmap_id>0x809add610073d241:0x4d060cd44f7fc6e7</gmap_id></record></dataset><record>

<Time>1618783182318< /Time><Pics>None< /Pics><username>Jonathan Moua</username><GmapID>0x809add610073d241:0x4d060cd44f7fc6e7< /GmapID>< Resp>

< Rating>
4</Rating>
< Review>
Went on a Sunday right when they opened (noon). We were a party of 3 and opted for the all you can eat bbq.

Staff are very friendly and nice. The service was good but not amazing. My water cup was never refilled and at the end of the meal, we had to go up to the counter to get their attention that we wanted to pay for our bill. Nothing major but for some folks that matters a lot. There were maybe three or four other parties in the restaurant during the time we spent there.

The interior seems new and is really nice. At the current moment (April 2021) they don‚Äôt seem fully open so there‚Äôs some bussing carts around that make the place look a little clunky. The area where we were seated was nice though.

The food is pretty good and they serve it to you in smaller to medium sized portions. They let us order 3 appetizers and 3 meats and when we finished they would let us order more, again 3 apps and 3 meats. They switch out the grill in between orders. All the meats we ordered were good - beef belly, brisket, bulgogi, and pork belly (marinated, sliced, normal). All the banchan (side dishes) were good.

For the appetizers I‚Äôd recommend the tteokbokki (spicy rice cake), green onion pancake, and japchae. We didn‚Äôt love the seafood tofu soup, dumplings (neither the boiled nor the deep fried were amazing), steamed egg, or the cheesy corn.

Overall a pretty pleasant experience. Would I come here again? Sure! But I‚Äôll have to be pretty adamant about asking for water refills.< /Review>

< Text>
I have been coming here for 40 years. It has been my go-to when craving Korean food. Today I notice it's changed ownership. The place has been remodeled and looks great new tables/ booths. The new owner talked with me for a good ten minutes. Service was great, every employee that walked by my table, made I contact and asked if I needed anything and how I was doing. I am not Korean not do I speak it short of the dishes I like. So to be treated this way as a solo diner who orders water.
Thank you for a great lunch. The food was spot on.</Text>

Hidden diamond of Korean food< /text>
< Pictures>

<rating>5<//rating></record>
</dataset><record>
<Time>1567542986700<//Time><gmap_id>0x809add610073d241:0x4d060cd44f7fc6e7</gmap_id>< pics>
None</pics>
< response>
None</response>
< Rate>
3< /Rate>
< text>
This place is nicely designed, clean and fresh looking. The seating in the back is a little awkward as the benches are pretty far from the table (about 2 1/2 feet?) so if you are a regular sized person you have to bend over at the table. The food is actually pretty good. We ordered the LA Galbi and it was around $16 about half the price of other similar places. Our biggest issues were two main areas. 1. The food took a long time to come out. We ordered the following LA Calbi (30 mins to come out), pancakes (25 mins to come out), cold noodles (20 mins to come out, wife said it was good), warm noodles and ramen (1+ hour to come out) and they messed up on the order and brought out the spicy warm noodles when we ordered the non-spicy one (for our kids). We reminded them 3-4 times and asked for updates during that time and was told each time it was coming. It got to a point where we we done eating and the kids still didn't eat yet. Also, don't order the ramen there, for $7.99 it was instant package ramen with one egg and nothing else (literally, no garnish, meats, anything). I was also interested in ordering the kebab stuff too and filled out a second menu (you have to fill it out and turn it in) and gave to the waitress and apparently she didn't put in my order. 2. The service, while they were nice, the wait staff's english wasn't passable. They struggled to communicate with us throughout the dinner. Especially when we were waiting so long for our food. The owner, the korean lady came out and figured out they messed up and gave us (and other tables) 2 free sodas and a few bag of chips for the kids and said sorry. That's why it's a 3 star review instead of a 1. Not sure if I would come back here with my family and wouldn't recommend it at this point until they correct their issues.<//text>

Our experience tonight was quite a bummer. Placed an order online (giant cheesesteak with extra cheese) and paid with a gift card. Pickup time was 6:13 and my husband arrived at 6:15, at which point he was informed that they were out of bread. They said it would be another five minutes, but he didn't get out of there until 6:35. Now, we get it - things happen and they were obviously busy. But this was particularly irritating because my husband had called just a few minutes before the pickup time to confirm that he ordered extra cheese. They confirmed that he did, but didn't think to mention that they were running 20 minutes behind on their online orders? That would have been a nice detail to share, especially because you'd think they would want to avoid making customers wait in their shop for so long during a pandemic if they could avoid it. The cherry on top? When we unwrapped the sandwich at home, there was a black hair tucked in with it. It was on the shorter side, so we assume it belonged to a dark haired man. Perhaps hairnets are in order? Overall, the experience was a major bummer - a waste of twenty bucks, and twenty minutes of my husband's time since we couldn't even stomach the thought of eating the sandwich after finding the hair.<//text>

I always enjoy Jersey Mike's. Amazing sandwiches, friendly and helpful staff. Everything done the way you like, nothing bad to say about this place. One thing I recently learned after coming here for years is they have a bit of a secret menu for some items, which is done by taking a couple select items on the menu and combining them, by adding there numbers, so for example you like the Big Kahuna #56, but you also like the Chipotle Cheese Steak #43, and wish the Big Kahuna had that chipotle on it. Very good restaurant! < user_name>
V. V. Steele</user_name>
<Date>1582517636332<//Date><rating>5<//rating>< Text>
The food was incredibly good. I grew up on the east coast where Italian restaurants are prevalent like Mexican food restaurantsis here on the west coast. It is difficult to find an Italian restaurant with the feeling of being family while you are there & a menu offering authentic Italian food but we managed to find both of those elements at Caffe Giostra.
At the last minute, on Christmas Eve, my friend & I wanted to try a restaurant, just up the road from where he lives, technically in Penngrove but some would say Petaluma. I called to see if they happened to have a table available but they were packed & for good reason, as we soon found out. I then made a reservation for about an hour & a half later but unfortunately the couple at the table we reserved decided to stay & chat long after they were finished with their meal. It seemed to me like they were on a first date. So instead, we were warmly invited to order our dinner to go, which wasnt a big deal, neither of us minded in the least. We were happy that they were open on Christmas Eve & that we were going to eat a meal from somewhere other then a fast food restaurant. They had a wonderful selection of items on a special Christmas menu. We were both happy with our entrees, as well as with the Caesar salad & dessert that we shared. We will definately be eating there again.
Absolutely 5 stars ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê</Text>

< Review>
Food is amazing. I have been here maybe 8-10 times. If my only criteria was food, then it's a 5. But the service here is probably the worst I have experienced. And it's consistently disappointing. They always overbook the place. Probably why you have to wait so long every time. After going today, I will never be returning which is a shame. Like I said, the food is wonderful. But after making reservations for 6:30 and being seated at 7:05 (which happens almost every time, 15 minutes late was the best they have ever done) I was already off to a bad start. Then they waited to within 5 minutes of our food arriving to finally remember to bring our drinks and bread. They didn't tell us about the specials and never came back to fill my water once. The chefs in this place are amazing. The lady cleaning up the tables and bringing bread (black hair in her 20s) was the most hospitable person there. She was very nice. But the short lady waiter is consistently rude and forgets things I ask for. I think she may be part owner or something but she awful.<//Review>

108900579328582984523</userid>
<user_name>Scott Schang</user_name><Time>1576014610950</Time><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
It takes more than just a good product to impress me. I want to know that the people behind the product share my values, vision and passion for delivering a best in class consumer experience!  LeadPops checks all of these boxes.

I have been blogging about Real Estate and Mortgages since 2007.  When I started, I didn't really understand lead capture or conversion.  For many of the early years I used form builders like Gravity Forms or Woo Forms to convert readers into customers.

What initially attracted me to LeadPops was the book that founder and CEO, Andrew Pawlak wrote called The Mortgage Marketing Manifesto: Unlocking the Holy Grail of Mortgage Lead Generation.

At this point, I had been creating consumer direct content for years.  I was having some degree of success converting that traffic.  LeadPops for me was definitely "the next level".  It was clear by reading Andrew's book that he truly understood conversion and was a master at his craft.  I had no idea.

The last major update I made to my web properties was in 2017.  Looking at it now, there are a bunch of things I could have done better, but by following LeadPops best practices my traffic to lead conversion went from approximately 1% to 2.5% to 3%.  10k unique visitors is not unusual for my website.  What used to result in around 100 leads a month off that traffic was catapualted to 200+ leads a month on average.  That's huge.

After collecting over 5,300 leads using LeadPops, I am still amazed at the pullthrough rates once someone click on the lead form.  My best performing funnels have converted almost 2,000 leads at over a 10% click to complete rate!  Again, this is unheard of.

Online marketing has a lot of moving parts.  Being able to tap into the expertise and vision at LeadPops has been an invaluable ingredient in our recipe for success.

I cannot recommend LeadPops highly enough. Thank you caring enough to create amazing products!< /review>
